                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[From Plex to Pi-hole: The Software That Made My Homelab Feel Complete]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/from-plex-to-pi-hole-the-software-that-made-my-homelab-feel-complete/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/a-mini-pc-with-the-plex-logo.jpg" length="641" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Homelab]]></category><category><![CDATA[Self Hosted]]></category><category><![CDATA[Plex]]></category><category><![CDATA[Pi-Hole]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It's taken years, but my homelab finally feels complete.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I’ve been building out my homelab for nearly half a decade. It's involved many iterations; from hardware to software the makeup of my homelab has all changed many times over the years.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 18:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/from-plex-to-pi-hole-the-software-that-made-my-homelab-feel-complete/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Get 27% Off This Galaxy Book 5 360 Laptop With a 15-inch Screen Today]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/get-27-off-this-galaxy-book-5-360-laptop-with-a-15-inch-screen-today/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/samsung-galaxy-book5-360.jpg" length="200" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Deals]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A great price for a high-end convertible PC laptop.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you need a new Windows laptop with enough space for all your work, look no further than the Samsung Galaxy Book 5 360. It’s a 2-in–1 convertible laptop with a 15.6-inch screen on sale for $987, a discount of 27% from the original price of $1,350.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 17:49:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/get-27-off-this-galaxy-book-5-360-laptop-with-a-15-inch-screen-today/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google is Pulling Its Weather App on Wear OS Smartwatches]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-pulling-weather-app-on-wear-os-smartwatches/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joe Fedewa]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Google-Weather-icon.png" length="1202058" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Wear OS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel Watch]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Why is Google so weird about weather apps?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Google has a weird history with weather apps. Pretty much every phone comes pre-installed with a weather app, but for a long time, Google <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/884681/hey-google-its-time-to-make-a-real-weather-app/" target="_blank">simply didn't have one</a>. However, it did have a weather app that any Wear OS smartwatch could install. That app is going away, and the replacement is not straightforward.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 17:26:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-pulling-weather-app-on-wear-os-smartwatches/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Best Boomboxes of 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/789900/the-best-boomboxes/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Joy Okumoko]]></dc:creator><dc:creator><![CDATA[Kris Henges]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/52637090951_1da3ce64d6_o.jpg" length="282" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[buying guide]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Do you miss the humble boombox? Well, they never went away, and they've never been more feature-packed.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The original boomboxes offered one of the first ways to bring music anywhere. We've got plenty of options for portable music now, but a boombox brings more than that, with plenty of features, playback options, and volume.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 16:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/789900/the-best-boomboxes/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Apple Watch Will Tell You if You Have Hypertension]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-watch-will-tell-you-if-you-have-hypertension/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/apple-watch-ultra-2-showing-running-distances.jpg" length="112" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple Watch]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            It may not be a doctor, but it's getting pretty close.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Apple has officially received FDA approval for a new hypertension notification feature on its Apple Watch that’s rolling out next week. The best part is that you won't need to buy a new watch to get it. The feature is coming with the watchOS 26 update.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 16:00:21 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/apple-watch-will-tell-you-if-you-have-hypertension/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why the New iPhone Takes Better Selfies Than Your Android]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-everyone-should-copy-apples-new-front-facing-iphone-camera/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Tim Brookes]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/iphone-17-group-selfie.jpg" length="2863" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone 17 Pro]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple iPhone Air]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[photography]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Coming to an Android phone near you.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>While a lot of fanfare has been made about the iPhone’s new 48 megapixel rear-facing camera sensors, the front-facing shooter might be just as significant of a change, even if you don’t take a heap of selfies.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-everyone-should-copy-apples-new-front-facing-iphone-camera/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Linux Mint's Debian 13 Upgrade Is on the Way]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-mints-next-update-will-use-debian-13/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jorge A. Aguilar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/linux-mint-logo-on-a-default-background.jpg" length="36" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[Linux Mint]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Linux Mint Debian Edition (LMDE) is getting a new foundation, and Mint 22.3 is coming soon.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The Linux Mint team has explained the roadmap for their next major release, the Linux Mint Debian Edition 7 (LMDE 7), codenamed "Gigi." The regular edition of Linux Mint will stay on an Ubuntu base, but LMDE 7 will soon use the latest Debian 13 release as its foundation.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 15:42:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/linux-mints-next-update-will-use-debian-13/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Is the Apple Tax Still Real?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/is-the-apple-tax-still-real/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/03/iphone-16e-lockscreen-in-front-of-window-1.jpg" length="1964" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Iphone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apple]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPad]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Are all Apple products overpriced, or is it just a meme?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Apple has advertised itself as a premium brand for years, and just like every other premium brand, many people see its products as overpriced. There’s even a common name for it: the “Apple Tax.” Is that really true, though?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 15:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/is-the-apple-tax-still-real/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Google Home Just Got Two Huge Automation Features]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/google-home-just-got-two-huge-automation-features/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Arol Wright]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/a-hand-holding-a-google-nest-speaker.jpg" length="426" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Home]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Automate all the things.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you have smart home hardware compatible with Google Home, it's a tremendously useful tool to have. And now, it's about to get a huge automation update that will make your life a lot easier.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 14:36:41 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/google-home-just-got-two-huge-automation-features/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[6 Settings to Reduce Eye Strain on Windows]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/settings-to-save-eyes-windows/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/53109373160_102bc9c093_o.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[customization]]></category><category><![CDATA[Blue Lightning]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Let your eyes relax!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Do you often finish your workday with strained, tired eyes and worry about the long-term impact of high screen time on your vision? If so, adopting a few simple habits and using the right settings can help protect your eye health. Here’s how you can reduce eye strain and avoid those nagging headaches.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 14:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/settings-to-save-eyes-windows/</guid></item></channel>
